  "zh:CRISPR Gene Editing: Promise, Constraints, and Responsible Use": "CRISPR 基因编辑：承诺、限制和负责任的使用",
  "zh:Please recall everything you can from the article in 3 minutes, describing how CRISPR works, its medical and agricultural applications, key limitations, and ethical or governance challenges.": "请在 3 分钟内回忆文章中的所有内容，描述 CRISPR 的工作原理、其医学和农业应用、主要局限性以及伦理或治理挑战。",
  "zh:CRISPR—Cas technology re-purposes a bacterial immune system into a programmable gene-editing tool. A guide RNA directs the Cas enzyme to a chosen DNA sequence, where cellular repair can delete, insert, or correct genetic material. Its appeal lies in speed and low cost, yet precision is layered: off-target edits may arise when similar genomic regions are cut unintentionally. Researchers now refine guide design, engineer high-fidelity enzymes, and employ base or prime editors that swap letters without double-strand breaks. Delivery remains the toughest barrier—viral vectors, lipid nanoparticles, and new biodegradable carriers must reach the right tissues without provoking immunity. In medicine, ex vivo editing corrects blood-cell disorders under laboratory control, while in vivo applications for organs such as brain or heart demand higher safety. Germ-line editing of embryos remains largely prohibited because risks transmit to future generations. Agriculture uses CRISPR to strengthen crops and reduce pesticide use, requiring transparent regulation and public trust. Ethical oversight must balance innovation with equity through inclusive review boards, data openness, and long-term monitoring. Emerging editors, self-limiting delivery systems, and global governance frameworks will shape the next decade. CRISPR's success will be judged less by technical speed than by fairness, safety, and the integrity with which societies choose what to edit.": "CRISPR—Cas 技术将细菌免疫系统重新设计为可编程基因编辑工具。引导 RNA 将 Cas 酶引导至选定的 DNA 序列，细胞修复可以在其中删除、插入或纠正遗传物质。它的吸引力在于速度和低成本，但精度是分层的：当相似的基因组区域被无意切割时，可能会出现脱靶编辑。研究人员现在改进了指南设计，设计了高保真酶，并采用碱基编辑器或引物编辑器来交换字母而不会出现双链断裂。传递仍然是最艰难的障碍——病毒载体、脂质纳米粒子和新的可生物降解载体必须到达正确的组织而不激发免疫力。在医学上，离体编辑可以在实验室控制下纠正血细胞紊乱，而大脑或心脏等器官的体内应用则需要更高的安全性。胚胎的种系编辑在很大程度上仍然被禁止，因为风险会传递给后代。农业利用 CRISPR 来强化作物并减少农药的使用，需要透明的监管和公众信任。道德监督必须通过包容性审查委员会、数据开放和长期监控来平衡创新与公平。新兴编辑、自我限制的交付系统和全球治理框架将塑造下一个十年。评判 CRISPR 的成功的标准将不是技术速度，而是社会选择编辑内容的公平性、安全性和完整性。",
  "zh:- CRISPR—Cas re-purposes bacterial immunity to cut and repair specific DNA sequences.\n- Guide RNA directs Cas to target genes for editing or correction.\n- Off-target effects occur when similar sites are cut unintentionally.\n- High-fidelity, base, and prime editors reduce unwanted mutations.\n- Delivery via viruses, nanoparticles, or polymers is the main technical bottleneck.\n- Ex vivo editing suits blood disorders; in vivo aims at organs like heart or brain.\n- Germ-line embryo editing is banned in most nations due to heritable risk.\n- Agricultural uses enhance resilience but need transparent, equitable regulation.\n- Ethical governance requires inclusive oversight, data sharing, and global cooperation.\n- Future success depends on fairness, safety, and responsible societal choice.\n": "- CRISPR—Cas 重新利用细菌免疫来切割和修复特定 DNA 序列。\n- Guide RNA 将 Cas 引导至目标基因进行编辑或校正。\n- 当相似的网站被无意中剪切时，就会出现脱靶效应。\n- 高保真、碱基和主编辑器可减少不需要的突变。\n- 通过病毒、纳米颗粒或聚合物进行传递是主要的技术瓶颈。\n- 离体编辑适合血液疾病；体内针对心脏或大脑等器官。\n- 由于存在遗传风险，大多数国家禁止生殖系胚胎编辑。\n- 农业用途增强了抵御能力，但需要透明、公平的监管。\n- 道德治理需要包容性监督、数据共享和全球合作。\n- 未来的成功取决于公平、安全和负责任的社会选择。",
